channel.title: Forum Member of the Week - 07: ToxicCaves64
channel.description:
<big> Featured Auxy Artist #07: @TC64 </big>
![29%20PM|690x218](upload://ttJQzC4aLCPe2pSkNuE7DtVExiv.jpg)
<big>ToxicCaves64</big> (a.k.a T.C Music) produces Chiptunes, synth funk, and other sweet sounds with Auxy and Ableton. During October 2017 ("Auxtober") he released a track each day. If you haven't heard them, then you're in for a treat - [check it out](https://soundcloud.com/toxiccaves64/sets/auxtober-the-best-songs). And if that's not enough for you, look what he can make with only [five Auxy instruments](https://soundcloud.com/toxiccaves64/hyper-ultra-light-speed). TC64 got talent.
**Week starting: 12 Feb, 2018.** - Please listen to at least one of their tracks (or more) - Provide at least one Soundcloud comment / feedback about their music during their week. - Comment in this thread once you've provided any feedback.
Check out their tracks here: https://soundcloud.com/toxiccaves64/tracks
If you want to be in the weekly draw [add your name.](https://disco.auxy.co/t/forum-member-of-the-week-who-wants-to-be-involved/5518)
![3385_1|120x120](upload://jRavGtmH2lvevOo6wh5br4mUHrf.png)

item.title: Forum Member of the Week - 07: ToxicCaves64
item.dc:creator: Sunny
item.description:
My biggest thoughts on your music, @TC64 is that it’s cute, but detailed. Strong leads, good mixing, fun drums. I especially liked the funk you had posted from about a year ago, but no song jumped into mind since they the tracks overall were a bit repetitive, but you tapped into something cool there that might be worth revisiting.

My faves:

Silver was dope. It was super fun, and I enjoyed the vocal-like sounds. I would just keep some drum beats going for longer in parts. Let me enjoy, darn you.

Lantern: Man is that twig? God I love twig, just adds this weird acoustic sound. I enjoyed all the variations this songs went through.

Leev ft. USDebt just had a wonderful melody. In fact, a lot of the songs chronologically before that have really cute melodies. You should continue to explore that, I really enjoyed it!

Evolve was probably my fave out of your funk entries, and it’s very similar to Gase, which would make the former its natural progression.

Read full topic

item.dc:creator: TC64
item.description:
The “Toxic Caves” is a level in a SEGA game that has some great music with a funky style that ended up inspiring some of the songs I’ve made.

Since I grew up with games like Super Mario 64, I ended my username with “64” to add on to the general video game theme that my music has.

P.S. Yeah, Odyssey is my jam.
